cho_description:
12th dynasty wooden model of funeral barge: The hull is shallow, with narrow beam; graceful curve to sheer-line. Deck slightly hollowed out, leaving low gunwales which merge into bow and stern; the two latter have the ornamental finials usual in funeral barges.

Length: 77.5 centimetres Width: 13.4 centimetres Depth: 6 centimetres

COL: http://www.britishmuseum.org/research/collection_online/collection_object_details.aspx?partId=1&objectId=125320

Co-created model with photomasking by @micropasts contributors. Missing some photographs due to speed of capture and no chance to turn over. Model created from 190 photos (taken with Nikon D5100) by Daniel Pett.
